verbose_text: Baek et al reported that DYRK1A along with down syndrome candidate region 1 (DSCR1), which encodes a protein that suppresses vascular endothelial growth factor (VEGF)-mediated angiogenic signaling by the calcineurin pathway, may be sufficient to markedly diminish angiogenesis.
